Aeman Presley , 34, faces charges for the killing of two homeless men in Atlanta and a hairdresser in Decatur . 
  He originally set out to rob his victims but was overcome with 'bloodlust' after killing Calvin Gholston , 53 . 
  He then shot Dorian Jenkins , 42, and Tommy Mims , 68, while they slept outside . 
  He also shot Karen Pearce , 44, in a parking garage on her way home from dinner . 
  Presley said he wanted to go back to acting but was arrested for jumping a turnstile . 
 